did.unittitle: George Washington University Publications collection
did.abstract: This is an artificial collection composed of printed materials acquired by Special Collections Reearch Center at various times. The collection was created in 2019 from original MARC records. The collection printed materials and paper documents published by the George Washington University. The publications date generally from 1924-2017.
did.physloc: Materials are stored off-site, and will require additional retrieval time. Please contact the Special Collections Research Center for more information.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: This collection is composed of publications or portions of publications and other printed materials. This is an artificial collection created in 2019 by repurposing MARC data. These materials were originally item level records in the library's ILS. With the creation of the resource record the MARC records were withdrawn from the ILS. Each item includes a general note that contains the original call no., 5xx and 6xx field data.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: This is an artificial collection composed of printed materials acquired by Special Collections Research Center at various times. The collection was created in 2019 from original MARC records.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection is composed of publication, portions of publicatons and other printed materials. These materials were originally individually cataloged and managed in the library's ILS. The primary subject of the materials relates to the schools and departments of the University. The items date from approximately 1924-2017.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Materials in this collection may be governed by copyright. For activities that the researcher determines fall under fair use as defined under U. S. Copyright Law, no permission to cite or publish is required. Researchers are responsible for determining who may hold materials' copyrights, determining if the intended re-use falls under fair use, and obtaining approval from the copyright holder if the intended use does not fall under fair use. Please contact Special Collections if the copyright status of the materials you wish to reuse is unclear. Staff will provide additional information.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way: Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository. Example: James Oglethorpe to the Trustees, 13 January 1876, RG0001 Series 1, Box 4, Folder 3. Records of the Board of Trustees, Special Collections Research Center, Gelman Library, The George Washington University, Washington, D.C.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The publications are grouped by which department or school created the publication. Otherwise, they are grouped by topic.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The publications acquired over many years from different sources.
